{
  "stem": "27748.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, she instead-- instead of clipping coupons, she decided to do something with her life.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she created a business, an international business of embroidery.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She employed 250 people, and so on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then when Hitler came to power, she went to England and decided to devote herself to bringing Jews out of Germany, and getting them on their feet, this German woman.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But she was educated, and knew English, and so on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she established a guest house in London, where people stayed, but also-- also, like a restaurant, could have meals there without staying there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she always had some people there that she had brought out who stayed at her house until they got on their feet, until they found work.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she took some people under her wing who had come out in other ways, not through her, and sort of got them on their feet.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she took on a number of children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I became one of those children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The reason for that is a person who worked for her as a cook was a cousin.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My first cousin worked for her as a coop.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, in addition, this Mrs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Karger had a nephew who was in the same school where I was at Bunce Court.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was how the connection became established, and how I became to her attention.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So what then happened, after I left Bunce Court and went to London in 1943, when I was 20-- when I was 15, I went to London.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She helped me find a job.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't stay at her house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was then transferred from the refugee organization to a kind of a Jewish [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] philanthropic-- it was called the Board of Guardians, became my legal guardians in London.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
